4. Important Features of GLM-5.2
The model card lists several major highlights:

a) 1M Token Context Window
GLM-5.2 supports a 1,000,000 token context, which means it can process a very large amount of text/code in one session. This is useful for:

long PDFs

large codebases

project documentation

long conversations and memory-heavy tasks

b) Strong Coding Capability
The model is designed for coding and software engineering tasks, including longer and more difficult workflows than ordinary chat models.

c) Agentic / Long-Horizon Task Support
GLM-5.2 is presented as a model for “long-horizon tasks,” meaning it is intended to work through tasks that involve multiple steps, tools, or extended context.

d) Open Weights + MIT License
The model is released with an MIT license, making it more open and accessible for research and development use.

e) Architecture Improvements
The model card mentions:

IndexShare for more efficient sparse attention at long context

an improved MTP layer for speculative decoding and better acceptance length

These improvements aim to make long-context processing and inference more efficient. 

